        "Name": "Fer-De-Lance",
        "Details": "Developed by Majesty Metals and Manufacturing on Canopus IV, the Fer-de-Lance is a homegrown Canopian Star League-era BattleMech design. The Fer-de-Lance FDL-3U is a rare fire-support variant of the design. It reduces the ground speed to a mere 110 kph, courtesy of a 210-rated XL engine, and builds the mech with both Endo-Steel and Ferro-Fibrous construction materials. All this free tonnage is put towards an Ultra Autocannon/5 with two tons of ammunition, giving the Fer-de-Lance an unexpected punch for its size. A pair of Small Lasers provide backup in emergencies. The Fer-de-Lance managed to survive the Succession Wars in decent numbers and remains a staple of the Magistracy Armed Forces.<br><br>X-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
